    <fieldset>
      <legend>Tasting Room <br/>& Wine Shop</legend>
      <p>
        After many years of homebrewing mead, Cris and Kent Slaymaker decided to make the switch to commercial
        mead making.  They built their basement into a licensed winery production space and founded
        Slaymaker Cellars in 2019.
      </p>
      <p>
        Our mead was well received and needed to grow, so we hired some folks to work with us. Slaymaker Cellars is
        now an award winning, Employee Owned Meadery.
      </p>
      <p>
        We offer mead, wine, cider, and more by the glass or in bottles to go.
        Let us know at the bar what you would like to try, or if you can't decide, check out our flights.
        We are happy to walk you through all of the options available.
      </p>
      <p>
        Taxes included in all prices.
      </p>
    </fieldset>

